<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<ContentPage xmlns="http://xamarin.com/schemas/2014/forms"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:prism="http://prismlibrary.com"
             prism:ViewModelLocator.AutowireViewModel="True"
             x:Class="FYMApp.Views.FoodActivity" BackgroundColor="#43548B">

    <ContentPage.Content>
        <StackLayout>
            <Label Text="Meal Time" 
                   FontSize="Large"
                   HorizontalOptions="Center"
                   TextColor="Black"/>

            <Frame CornerRadius="100"
                   IsClippedToBounds="True"
                   HeightRequest="500"
                    WidthRequest="200"
                    HorizontalOptions="CenterAndExpand"
                   Padding="0">
                <Image Source="bread.jpeg"
                       Aspect="Fill"
                   VerticalOptions="Center" 
                   HorizontalOptions="Center"/>
            </Frame>
            <ScrollView VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Always" VerticalOptions="FillAndExpand" Margin="10">
                <Label TextColor="White" FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="Medium">
                    <Label.Text>
                        -Establish a meal schedule for the duration of the day.
                        
-Allow children to partake in meal preparation such as setting the table. 
                        
-Teach children about table etiquette
                        
-Provide children with a variety of foods.
                        
-Promote locally bought and traditional food.
                        
-Provide children with small portions of food at a time allowing them to finish their food will give them a sense of achievement.
                        
-Encourage children to ask for more food instead of having too much food and then wasting it.
                        
                              Activity 1. EDLA; 1,3,5,6
                        
 Requirements
 -None

Exercise: Discussion

Discuss different types of food 
with children 
-Food Groups (Veg/Fruit)
-How it is harvest (Ground/Tree)
-Healthy vs. unhealthy

Activity 2. EDLA: 1,3,5,6

Requirements: 
-A3 Cardboard/Paper
-Magazines/Newspaper/Food wrappers
-scissor
-pritt/prestick/glue
-Crayons/Kokki/Colour pens

Exercise: Poster
-Allow children to identify different type of
food as discussed in previous exercise 
in magazines/newspaper
-Allow children to cut the food out paste it
in the relevant categories (as discussed in 
previous exercise)
-Make different types of posters
-Throughout exercise as open ended 
questions about the food eg:
- What type of fruit is this?
-Where does this food come from?
-Who likes this food?

Activity 3: EDLA 1,3,5,6

Requirements:
-None

Exercise: Sing
-Introduce children to different songs, 
nursery rhymes about food.
-Focus on a variety of songs including
traditional songs

Activity 4: EDLA, 1,3,5,6

Requirements:
-Empty shopping bags from local shops
-Empty plastic cooldrink bottles
-Empty food plastics eg, bread plastic
-Empty Egg box
-Old newspaper
-Plastic utensils
-Medium sized stones

Exercise: Role Play (Grocery Shopping/
Cooking)
-Group children 
-Allocate each child a role eg farmer, 
customer, store cashier
-Children to role play the different activities
that takes place in each area eg.
on the farm, food store, in the kitchen.
-This teaches child food ecosystem from 
the time of its production until its used in
their homes to make a meal.
-Sing songs, rhymes about food

Activity 5: EDLA 1,2,3,4,5,6,

Requirements:
-Different fruit/Vegetables

Exercise: Taste Testing
- Divide
                    </Label.Text>
                </Label>
            </ScrollView>
        </StackLayout>
    </ContentPage.Content>
  
</ContentPage>